allowance(address,address).details: Returns the remaining number of tokens that `spender` will be allowed to spend on behalf of `owner` through {transferFrom}. This is zero by default. This value changes when {approve} or {transferFrom} are called.

approve(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-approve}. NOTE: If `value` is the maximum `uint256`, the allowance is not updated on `transferFrom`. This is semantically equivalent to an infinite approval. Requirements: - `spender` cannot be the zero address.

balanceOf(address).details: Returns the value of tokens owned by `account`.

collectFees().details: Fees are minted as new shares to manager and protocol

returns._0: decimals Number of decimals matching the base asset

returns.weightsBps: Array of weights in basis points

returns.value: Total value in base asset units

params._baseAsset: Base asset for single-asset operations (e.g., USDC)

issueWithBase(uint256,uint256,address,bo.details: Swaps base asset to portfolio tokens and calculates shares based on actual value added

params.baseAmount: Amount of base asset to deposit
params.payFeeWithCRT: If true, pay fee with CRT token (50% discount)

returns._0: The address of the vault manager

name().details: Returns the name of the token.

params.baseAmount: Amount of base asset to deposit

returns.shares: Estimated shares to receive (may differ due to slippage)

rebalance(address,address,uint256,uint25.details: Requires CRT token payment (25 CRT = $0.50) sent to FeeCollector

rebalanceToWeights(address[],uint256[]).details: Requires CRT token payment (25 CRT = $0.50) sent to FeeCollectorSells excess tokens to baseAsset, then buys deficit tokens from baseAsset

params.targetWeightsBps: Target weights in basis points (must sum to 10000)
params.tokens: Target portfolio tokens (can include new tokens, exclude tokens to remove)

params.minBaseOut: Minimum base asset to receive (slippage protection)
params.payFeeWithCRT: If true, pay fee with CRT token (50% discount)

symbol().details: Returns the symbol of the token, usually a shorter version of the name.

totalSupply().details: Returns the value of tokens in existence.

transfer(address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transfer}. Requirements: - `to` cannot be the zero address. - the caller must have a balance of at least `value`.

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: See {IERC20-transferFrom}. Skips emitting an {Approval} event indicating an allowance update. This is not required by the ERC. See {xref-ERC20-_approve-address-address-uint256-bool-}[_approve]. NOTE: Does not update the allowance if the current allowance is the maximum `uint256`. Requirements: - `from` and `to` cannot be the zero address. - `from` must have a balance of at least `value`. - the caller must have allowance for ``from``'s tokens of at least `value`.

DEPOSIT_FEE_CRT_BPS().notice: Deposit fee in basis points when paying with CRT (50% discount)

DEPOSIT_FEE_USDC_BPS().notice: Deposit fee in basis points when paying with USDC

MIN_SHARES().notice: Minimum shares to prevent rounding issues

PERFORMANCE_FEE_BPS().notice: Performance fee in basis points (15% fixed)

PROTOCOL_PERF_FEE_BPS().notice: Protocol performance fee share in basis points (5% of total 15%)

REBALANCE_COST().notice: Rebalance cost in CRT tokens (represents $0.50 at TGE price $0.02)

STRATEGY_PERF_FEE_BPS().notice: Strategy performance fee share in basis points (10% of total 15%)

WITHDRAW_FEE_CRT_BPS().notice: Withdraw fee in basis points when paying with CRT (50% discount)

WITHDRAW_FEE_USDC_BPS().notice: Withdraw fee in basis points when paying with USDC

baseAsset().notice: The base asset for single-asset operations (e.g., USDC)

crtToken().notice: The MemeToken (CRT) contract for rebalance fees

decimals().notice: Returns the decimals for vault shares (same as base asset)

factory().notice: The factory that deployed this vault

feeCollector().notice: The FeeCollector contract for protocol fees

getPortfolioWeights().notice: Get portfolio weights in basis points

getTotalValue().notice: Get total portfolio value in base asset

highWaterMark().notice: High water mark for performance fee (NAV per share scaled by 1e18)

initializePortfolio(address[],uint256[],.notice: Initialize vault with initial portfolio (called by factory only)

initializeVault(string,string,address,ad.notice: Initialize the vault (called by factory via clone)

isPortfolioToken(address).notice: Mapping to check if a token is in portfolio

issue(uint256,address).notice: Issue shares by depositing tokens pro-rata

issueWithBase(uint256,uint256,address,bo.notice: Issue shares by depositing base asset (auto-swaps to portfolio)

managerTokenId().notice: The manager NFT token ID for this vault

portfolioTokens(uint256).notice: List of tokens in the portfolio

previewIssue(uint256).notice: Preview shares to receive for a given base asset deposit

previewRedeem(uint256).notice: Preview base asset to receive for redeeming shares

priceOracle().notice: The price oracle for token valuations

rebalance(address,address,uint256,uint25.notice: Rebalance by swapping one token for another (manager only)

rebalanceToWeights(address[],uint256[]).notice: Rebalance portfolio to target weights (manager only)

redeem(uint256,address).notice: Redeem shares for pro-rata portfolio tokens

redeemToBase(uint256,uint256,address,boo.notice: Redeem shares for base asset (swaps portfolio tokens)

swapRouter().notice: The swap router address (e.g., Uniswap V3 / Everyswap)
